{{Nihongo|'''Fukusai-ji'''|福済寺}} is an [[Ōbaku]] [[Zen]] temple in [[Nagasaki, Nagasaki|Nagasaki]], [[Nagasaki prefecture|Nagasaki]], [[Japan]]. Its honorary ''[[Buddhist temples in Japan#sangō|sangō]]'' prefix is {{nihongo|''Bunshizan''|分紫山}}. Founded in 1628 and later destroyed in 1945, Fukusai-ji has since been reconstructed in the shape of a turtle with an 18-metre high [[aluminium alloy]] statue of [[Kannon]], the [[Bodhisattva]] of compassion. The interior is famous for the 25-metre [[Foucault Pendulum]] which swings over the remains of 16,500 Japanese killed during [[World War II]].
