'''Henri Lauener''' (13 July 1933 in [[Bern]] - 28 October 2002, Bern) was a [[Swiss]] philosopher interested  in both transcendental and [[analytic philosophy|analytic]] currents.<ref name="Chisholm1985">{{cite book|last=Chisholm|first=Roderick M.|title=Philosophie des Geistes, Philosophie der Psychologie|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KD2aAAAAIAAJ|accessdate=4 May 2012|year=1985|publisher=Hölder-Pichler-Tempsky|isbn=978-3-209-00592-2|page=8}}</ref> He has been the editor of the journal ''[[Dialectica]]''. A ''Lauener Foundation for Analytical Philosophy'' has been developed, which awards a biennial prize to outstanding life works in this field.

