{{Korean name|Lee}} {{Infobox Korean name |hangul=이량 |hanja=李梁 |rr=Yi Ryang |mr=Lee Lyang |hangulja=공거 |hanjaja=公擧 |rrja=Gonggeo |mrja=Gongguh }} '''Lee Lyang'''([[korea]]n:이량, [[hanja]]:李梁, 1519&ndash;1583) was a [[Korea]]n [[Joseon Dynasty]] politician and a powerful man from the royal family [[Jeonju Lee clean]]'s. A descendant of [[Prince Hyoryeong]] and uncle of [[Queen Insun]], his [[courtesy name]] was '''Gonggeo'''(공거 公擧).
== Life == Lee Lyang was a member of the royal family of the [[Joseon Dynasty]], he was the great-great-great-grandson of [[Prince Hyoryeong]].<ref>Second son of Taejong of Joseon and brother of Sejong the great</ref> and his sister Lady Lee married to [[Shim Gang]]. Their daughter [[Queen Insun]] married to Prince Gyungwon, son of King [[Jungjong of Joseon|Jungjong]] and later King [[Myeongjong of Joseon|Myungjong]]. In his early years he studied at [[Chung Sa-ryong]]'s private academies.
In 1546 he passed to Saengwon and Chinsa exam. Also he was special recruitment appointed to bureaucrat. But he was passed to [[Imperial examination]] in 1552. He worked in a Joseon dynasty government office inspection department, the opinion department.
In 1550, King [[Myeongjong of Joseon|Myungjong]] was tension was Yun Won-hyung's take of government power and Lee Lyang was promoted rapidly under the auspices of King [[Myeongjong of Joseon|Myungjong]]s. But he was promoted to second level bureaucrat after only two years. But, he was illegally accumulate wealth. In 1563 he was ousted from [[Joseon Dynasty]]'s governments.
